Varga doesn't get up. She just looks at you for a long moment, the way you look at a debt you've written off. "You sold it. To the Syndicate. My drive, the one I sent you for." A thin, tired smile. "I'd ask if it was worth it, but you already counted the money. We're done — but the city's small, and I remember."
* [It was business.]
    "It always is. That's what makes it hurt less. Go on."
    -> END
* [Say nothing.]
    "No. I didn't think you would."
    -> END
